  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3507d679efa283143b52308c9a6a3292, type: 3}
  m_Name: Module_2_Set_Q3
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::QuestionData
  question: In which era did companies guide astronauts from Earth to the moon and
    advance to handle more than one kind of instruction?
  answers:
  - The Era of Tabulation
  - The Era of AI
  - The Era of Programming
  - The Era of Industrialisation
  maxSelections: 1
  correctAnswerIndices: 02000000
  correctMessage: During the turmoil of World War II, a new approach to data emerged,
    called the Era of Programming, that could run more than one kind of instruction
    (called "programs" today) in order to do more than one kind of calculation. Programmable
    computers guided astronauts from Earth to the moon during this era.
  incorrectMessage: During the turmoil of World War II, a new approach to data emerged,
    called the Era of Programming, that could run more than one kind of instruction
    (called "programs" today) in order to do more than one kind of calculation. Programmable
    computers guided astronauts from Earth to the moon during this era.
